name: Lebanon Hills Visitor Center
directions: Outdoors at the main building
comment: Free, open to the public

name: Zeal food for enthusiasts
comment: Two single stall gender neutral bathrooms.

name: Viva Vegeria
directions: The center of the restaurant

name: SAY SÃ­
directions: As soon as you walk in take a right and they will be in a little nook

name: New York University Department of English
directions: There is one single stall, gender neutral room on the first floor and another on the third floor.
comment: These are only accessible to NYU students.

name: Paradise Hills Branch Library
directions: Keys at front desk.

name: Maeve's Cafe
directions: Ground floor, toward the rear of the cafe, accessible via rear (parking area) door or from street.
comment: Maeve's is a safe, lively, community space for all races, gender identities, and religions. The sign at the front counter that says "Be nice or get out" says it all.

name: Wise Fool New Mexico
directions: It's straight back through the door that's in front of you after you enter the building through the side entrance.
comment: It is a small community, so if there's someone at the front desk when you go in, they might ask you what you're there for. But if you explain/introduce yourself, they will let you use the restroom.

name: HOURGLASS PUB
directions: In the arcade.
comment: We are a safe place.  If you need help or feel unsafe please don't hesitate to speak to any member of our staff.

name: UCSF Medical Sciences Building
directions: Third floor, near door to hospital

name: Wright Bros. Brew and Brew
directions: Behind the coffee bar

name: Brown University Visitor Center Faunce House
directions: Second floor right next to the elevators.
comment: If you have a hard time finding it, walk in the front door, continue toward the Blue Room Cafe. Then, go up the stairs or elevator right before you reach the seating area of the Blue Room, and the bathroom should be to your left at the top of the stairs or next to the elevator.

name: PLG Coffee House & Tavern
comment: Really friendly staff. It would help to be a paying customer but I can't imagine they'd stop you if you just used the bathroom.

name: PLG Coffee House & Tavern
comment: Really friendly staff. It would help to be a paying customer but I can't imagine they'd stop you if you just used the bathroom.

name: Fat Dragon
comment: For customers dining in or people at the bar

name: Wedge Community Co-op
directions: Against the east wall of the store, just past the produce and bulk sections

name: East Side Food Co-op
directions: To the left inside the front entrance

name: Target
directions: Immediately to the left of the main entrance

name: Gator's Grilled Cheese Emporium
directions: Two bathrooms at the front, both unisex and single user. Locks on door. One handicap accessible.
comment: You do not have to be a paying customer.

name: Buttermilk Handcrafted Food
directions: Restroom is near the back door.

name: Trader Joe's Shrewsbury
directions: Behind the customer service desk. Ask any employee and they'll direct you to the restrooms.
comment: Two individual stall bathrooms with "both gender" signs on them. Nobody will give you a hard time (or probably even notice) if you go in to use the bathroom and don't buy anything.

name: Crouse Hospital
directions: 1st Floor, West Tower Building, nest to the Chapel
comment: Must get visitor sticker or have employee badge to enter the hospital.

name: SuperTarget
directions: Located directly to the right of the pharmacy counter on the south side of the store.
comment: No additional advice needed as this restroom is in a Target store which has already shown friendliness to all guests.

name: First Unitarian Universalist Church of Syracuse
directions: in the hallway across from the parish hall (turn right when you enter, continue forward through the square room)
comment: church may not always be open, but if they are the people there will be happy to let you use the bathroom, it would be nice to talk to them though!

name: FAWN Food Pantry
directions: FAWN is located in the Frankford Shopping Plaza, next to PNC Bank
comment: FAWN is a safe space for all people. Staff are allies. Simply ask to use the facilities.

name: West elm
directions: Back of store by water fountain.

name: Pike Market Food Bank
directions: If you are in the market, go to the sky bridge and hit P5 to go to the food bank.

name: Intermedia Arts
directions: To the right of the kitchen / left of the stairs
comment: Say hi! The staff are great and super welcoming

name: Color Me Mine
directions: Green door just past the front counter on the right
comment: don't have to be a customer, just ask to use it

name: FringeArts
directions: past the restaurant and a little past the doors to the theater
comment: gendered, but inclusive.

name: Brookland's Finest Bar & Kitchen
directions: Back and to the left, by the lighted DC flag.
comment: Both gender neutral, single occupancy bathrooms with locks that show "vacant" or "in use" on the outside. Staff & owners are allies.

name: Philadelphia museum of art Perelman Buildinf
directions: Downstairs (basement) by the coat room
comment: You have to buy a ticket for the museum

name: Lane Medical Library, Stanford University
directions: Ground floor at base of staircase

name: Schilling Cider
directions: Through the door and all the way to the back, on the right wall.
comment: The bathroom farthest back is accessible. If it's a busy time nobody will notice if you're a paying customer or not.

name: Bar Clavel
directions: two bathrooms in the front, both are single person and gender neutral
comment: you may be able to use it without anyone saying anything, or just say you are waiting for a friend, most people who work there would also be welcoming (one employee encouraged the transition of both to gender neutral)

name: Swedish Mill Creek Emergency Department
directions: Multiple single stall unisex bathrooms throughout waiting room and within ED department.
comment: If you are a patient or family/visitor of a patient the bathrooms are available to you.

name: San Diego State University, Aztec Student Union
directions: First floor of the student union by Chipotle
comment: Extra-large single bathroom on the ground floor, locking door no stalls

name: Trader Joe's
street: Pruneyard Shopping Center, 1875 S Bascom Ave
directions: Through the stockroom doors beside the food sampling area. It's signposted.

name: Art Metropole
directions: Door mid store on the east side of the shop,  down a flight of stairs.  Two private rooms,  ungendered.
comment: The shop person can direct you if you need assistance locating the door.

name: 61 Local
directions: back of space. two restrooms. both single occupancy and neutral.

name: Bethany Public Library
directions: Next to the water fountain straight ahead as you enter both sets of automatic doors, beside the librarians' desks.
comment: No usage restrictions. There are two generically marked bathrooms. Each have their own sink and toilet and are lockable from the inside.

name: Starbucks
directions: 2 single stall unisex rooms in back right corner

name: La Mie Bakery
comment: You have to be a paying customer

name: Merle Hay Mall
directions: By the children's play structure, near Panda Express, Auntie Anne's Pretzels, and Scooter's
comment: They are labeled as "Family restrooms"

name: Bueno y sano
comment: Easy entrance, two unisex toilet rooms.

name: St. Mary's College of Maryland
directions: Many buildings on campus have gender neutral bathrooms.
comment: Several buildings on campus have gender neutral bathrooms.

name: Jimmie B. Keel Regional Library
directions: Main entrance - turn left just before the second set of automatic doors. Walk down to the end of the hallway and turn left. Two individual bathrooms between rooms C and D.
comment: Public library, open to all.

name: The Coin-Op
directions: First door on the left past the bar.

name: Walking Man Brewery
directions: Brewery is in basement - stairs outside

name: Miller Hall, University of Washington College of Education
directions: Fourth floor

name: UC Davis Shields Library
directions: 4th floor

name: USC Joint Educational Project
directions: First floor in the back.
comment: We primarily serve USC student volunteers but you will not be turned away.

name: Abingdon & Witney College
directions: Next to Reception in Courthouse building on Welch Way
comment: All bathrooms on campus are gender neutral cubicles, but only the toilets next to reception are accessible to the public without needing to sign in.

name: Kelvin Smith Library
directions: First floor, behind the elevators
comment: CWRU ID or other photo ID required to enter the building.

name: Games People Play
directions: Downstairs right across from the entrance.
comment: Sometimes it's locked. If that's the case, you need to go upstairs and grab the key. They're pretty cool about letting you use it if you're just hanging out to play a game or partake in a tournament but not actually buying anything; will probably say no if you come in JUST to use the bathroom.

name: Hotel Kabuki
directions: first floor, back towards the mall

name: Gearan Performing Arts Center
directions: First floor to the ri ght

name: Northwestern University, International Studies Building
directions: upstairs, take a right;
comment: This old house is an office building for Northwestern's International Studies, Business Institutions, and Latin American/Caribbean Studies programs, but the building is open 9am-5pm during the week. Nobody should bother you if come in because there's not really a front desk, but if they do, tell them you are here to see the International Studies instructor upstairs.

name: University of Oregon science library cafe (aka Allan Price Science Commons)
directions: Behind (south of) coffee vendor. Hard to find but it is for public use
comment: Door says "all gender". Not sure about accessibility, but it was built in 2016. Cafe is technically called Elements Ca-Fe but I dont think many people know that. No need to buy anything because it's part of the library. Long hours during school year

name: north
comment: Inside of a restaurant but you can ask to use the bathroom

name: Yale University Women's Center
directions: Open most afternoons & evenings except Saturdays.  Head in the door at the back of the lobby, turn left, and keep walking through down the hallway through several doors until you see the bathroom on the left. (If these directions are hard to follow, one of the friendly folks inside can give directions as well!)
comment: Center open to folks of all genders.

name: Berlin Bicycle Cafe
comment: Very open and comfortable space.

name: Voorhies Engineering Technology
directions: Middle section of the building, across from the Department Office, Rm 143  Single stall.

name: Santa Barbara Airport (SBA)
directions: In the main lobby across from the cafe.

name: Erb Memorial Union, University of Oregon
directions: Available on each floor.
comment: There are several gender neutral or all-gender restrooms throughout the EMU, as well as a student-run LGBTQA office on the ground floor.

name: Royal Drummer
directions: Back around the corner behind the coffee bar

name: Westfield Sarasota Square
directions: One single stall accessible toilet in the family area, right next to the indoor movie theater entrance by the food court.
comment: No need to be a customer. There might be young kids playing around in the family room, especially when it's busy or during season.

name: Evie's Tavern and Grill
directions: Single stall restrooms located outside only! If you're eating at the sports bar, go out the back doors to the outside bar and take a right. If you're at the arcade, do the same but take a left.
comment: You should probably be a customer to use these restrooms.

name: University Town Center
directions: There are bathrooms on the first and second floors located directly above/below each other. There are gendered restrooms and then one large, single-stall unisex restroom on each floor. During slow hours, the second floor restrooms are often sparsely populated.

name: Tijuana Flats
directions: In the back of the restaurant. Single stall gendered restrooms.

name: Publix
directions: Two gendered restrooms and one gender neutral accessible stall in between the gendered rooms. It's by the florist.

name: The Grey Dog
comment: *should* be a paying customer, but they're often busy enough/get enough traffic that walking with a purpose should be fine.

name: Culinary Institute of America
directions: On the main floor of the library. There's one women's and one gender neutral.

name: Mudsmith Coffee
directions: Enter the shop, go left of the serving counter.
comment: Restrooms are gender assigned, but single occupancy and locked. I BELIEVE they are accessible, but can't remember if there were supports/handrails on the walls.

name: Costco
directions: Front of the store
comment: Family restroom, single stall.

name: The YinOva Center
directions: Ask the Front Desk as you enter, they will show you where to go.
comment: We are an acupuncture clinic primarily and our bathrooms are for our patients. However, if you come in quietly and ask our front desk if you can use the restroom, they will happily show you the way. We just ask for quiet voices and respect of our clinic in return.

name: Animal Humane Society
directions: across the hallway from the cats with an upper respiratory infection; near the Education room
comment: you do not need to be intending to adopt an animal to visit this shelter, interact with the animals, or use its facilities

name: June's All Day
directions: Two single-stall gender neutral bathrooms toward the back left corner of the restaurant once you walk in.
comment: They are for customers, however you can always stop in for a quick coffee or to look at the menu or something and ask to use the restroom. <3

name: Charis Books and More
directions: back, right of main bookstore area

name: Mei Mei Restaurant
directions: Two gender neutral restrooms to the right of the counter.
comment: They prefer that you are a paying customer - if you aren't dining, buy an iced drink, cute single service soy sauce, or sticker from their retail shelf (all $3.21 and under).

name: The Whitney
directions: on "education" level there is an all gender restroom as well as gendered.
comment: unless you have a membership, you do have to pay to get in, but while you're there it's good to know about

name: Drake Theater
directions: Go through the lobby, turn right, and you'll find many unisex stalls.

name: Coquette
directions: One downstairs near kitchen, one upstairs
comment: Probably have to be a paying customer.
